column1: [1] [Components] | Sembcorp plant (5.1 million m3), The APUA Camp Blizzard Plant (1.0 million m3), The Ffryes Beach Reverse Osmosis Plant (1.0 million m3). Barbuda (0.04 million m3)
[2] [Components] | Production of over 200 small reverse osmosis plants included
[3] [Components] | Production of the major plant in St. Michael
[5] [Observations] | All desalinated water is used by municipalities.
[6] [Reference Area] | There are four desalination plants, two on Mahe Island, one on Praslin Island and one on La Digue Island.
